adviseScripts.text: Lookie here, a rabbit!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: And over there, a rabbit!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: There are so many rabbits here, I'm so happy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'm happy too, because you're here.
I guess you don't need me around anymore then.
Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Even if I'm surrounded by other rabbits,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I like being around you the most, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What? Of course not!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Why would you say that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I like being around you the most, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I admire the bunnies at Coin Rush.
I want to get a present for Nanook and Pigeon.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What do you think would be good?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Some cotton candy in the shape of a rabbit.
You yourself make a fine present.
Whoa, I didn't even know that was a thing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That sounds fantastic!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I knew you'd come up with something great, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: How could I be a present?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I think I ought to consider something else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I brainstorm what gifts to get for Neve and Tove.
It's been so much fun seeing Twinkling Bunny these past few days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I want to keep seeing her,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: but I guess that's not possible, huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I could suggest that Soda move up north and live with you.
You can invite her to come over wherever you're living.
What? Move up north?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... As much as I'd like that, I don't think it's possible.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: She twinkles the most when she's at the Maid Cafe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Oooh, that's a good idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll invite her and her friends to come visit me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: and we can have a grand old time playing together!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You'll come too, won't you, Rabbity?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Alice about Soda.
Ever since I came here,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I've been dazzled by all the sparkly things!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The North is full of sparkly things too. The snow, for one.
Should we try and snitch something sparkling?
You're right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The snow that the Snow Queen makes sparkles a lot too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's why I like it so much!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Why do we need to do that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Up north, where the Snow Queen's snow falls, it sparkles so much that it's really pretty!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about sparkly things.
Twinkling Bunny invited me to the Maid Cafe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What should I eat when I go there?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Everything on the menu.
Carrot cake.
Huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: All of it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I can't do that. If I did, my belly would end up exploding.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Holy moly!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: They make carrot cake over there?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I bet it's delicious! I'll be sure to have a slice!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I recommend a few menu items from the Maid Cafe to Alice.
Hey, Rabbity! Can I tell you something?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I really like you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I like you more.
I like you too.
What?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: No way!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I like you the most!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: You do?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Wow, that means you must really like me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: cause I reaaaaaalllly like you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a great time together.
I've been wondering
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: why is Slippery Bunny always leaking water?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's her sweating. She gets overheated easily.
She's actually the Water Queen.
Oh, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I should ask the Queen to make it snow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That'd probably help cool her off, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Whoa, no kidding?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I should introduce her to the Snow Queen.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Alice about Folkwang.
Hey, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Since I've become a rabbit, do you wanna have a race?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll take you on.
Sorry, but I'm not up for it.
Hehe, okay!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Go!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Are you worried that you'll fall asleep halfway through?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Don't worry, I'll wake you up!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Let's run together, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a race.
Let's play the Jingle Jingle game!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Jingle Jingle game?
*Jingle jingle*
Tah-dah!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: How many coins do you think are in here?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Three?
Two?
Wrong!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Since it jingled twice, the answer is two.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: If you had guessed correctly, I was gonna give you these coins as a reward.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Actually, since I really like you, I'll give them to you anyway!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Bingo!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: It jingled twice, so the answer is two.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Since you got it right, these coins are all yours!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: ... I should return these coins to Alice later.
Rabbity,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I want to get Twinkling Bunny a present.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What do you think would make her happy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The luck of a rabbit.
Some cleaning supplies.
Hmm... how can I give her that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Do I have to dance like the black and white bunnies?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... she already seems to have a lot of those.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything else she'd like more than cleaning supplies?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I brainstorm what gifts to get for Soda.
Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I had a dream last night where a bunch of rabbits appeared.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What do you think it means?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Sounds like a dream a dog would have.
An auspicious dream.
You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Wouldn't a dog dream of other dogs?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... the next time I dream, I'll have to see if any dogs show up or not!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll head to bed straight away and let you know how it goes!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Nice!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I wanna dream it again.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'm gonna go to sleep quickly!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I wish Alice sweet dreams.
Rabbity,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: what do you think the Queen is doing right now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Thinking about you.
Having tea.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, that makes me really happy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'm thinking about her too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Do you think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Thinking about tea time makes me miss the Queen...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Alice talking about Ludmilla.
I become so happy whenever I see the white and black bunnies!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Just looking at them lifts my spirits.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Maybe that's why they're lucky bunnies!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I feel happier whenever I see you too.
Do you want to become a lucky bunny too?
Wow, really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'm so flattered that I can make you happy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I'll stick by your side from here on out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... Not really.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Just having those two is plenty enough!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Being by your side fills me with boundless joy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about the lucky bunnies.
I like Doctor Rabbit!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: She's so kind and gentle!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I bet you won't even feel a thing when she gives you the injection!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I don't know about that...
You're right. It doesn't hurt at all.
But she's so considerate!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I bet you won't even feel a thing when she gives you an injection!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I knew it, hehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's because she's so considerate!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: She's always been that way, even before—
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Wait... before...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice?
I dunno, I've got this strange feeling... that I used to know Mary?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Maybe it's because I like her so much!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about Mary.
Rabbity.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What do you think it would be like if my Queen becomes a rabbit as well?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Then she'd become Device Demolisher Bunny.
Then she'd become Snow Queen Bunny.
Device Demolisher Bunny?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I don't get it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Don't you think she'd become something more like a Queen Bunny?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Ooooh!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That sounds so cool!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about Ludmilla.
Sweep, sweep!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: What are you up to, Alice?
Hey, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'm playing a cleaning game that I learned from Twinkling Bunny!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Am I doing a good job sweeping?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: There's still some trash left over there...
Are you interested in being a maid sometime?
Whoops!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Ah, got it! Teehee. I'll have to play the cleaning game again over there later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for pointing that out, Rabbity!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: A maid?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: If I were a maid, I could play cleaning games outside
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: with Twinkling Bunny and her friends.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That'd be great!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I play some cleaning games together.
Seeing the Boss gets me so excited!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: He's such a wonderful
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: song and dance man!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Mustang can sing?
Oh yes! Would you like to have a listen?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: No, that's okay.
Certainement, I'd like to listen.
Why not?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The Boss is really good at singing,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I promise!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll ask him to sing for us sometime.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Whoa, you sound just like Boss!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, this is exciting!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'll go and ask him to sing for us right now!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I calm down the excited Alice, who's just about to run off in search of Mustang.
Golden Bunny's friend, Red Fan, told me
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: that of all the things that shine bright, money shines the brightest.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Do you feel that way too, Rabbity?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Of course, nothing beats money.
Nope, snowflakes sparkle more.
Is that so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Personally, I feel that the Snow Queen's snowflakes are more sparkly,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: but I could be wrong...
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I think so too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Snow Queen's snowflakes are
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: so pretty and sparkly!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about sparkly things.
Rabbity,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: what flavor of carrot could you really go for right now?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I'm not in the mood for carrots right now.
A cotton candy-flavored carrot.
Huh? Why not?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Do you not like carrots anymore?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: All the carrots in the world are gonna be so sad!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Wow, there's a flavor like that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Sounds scrumptious!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice and I have a conversation about delicious carrots.
Hippity hop!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Alice is hopping around by herself.
What are you up to, Alice?
Since I'm now a rabbit, I've been practicing my hopping.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: The only thing is that I can't seem to jump very high.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: That's because it's still early in your practice.
That's because you're a Nikke...
You're right, it's probably because I haven't gotten enough practice in.
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, got it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: So long as I've got these rabbit ears and tail,
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: one day, I'll be able to hop hiiiiiigh in the sky!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Isn't that right, Rabbity?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Huh? No, no, no, I'm a rabbit!
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Can't you see these rabbit ears of mine?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: And my rabbit tail?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: Isn't it obvious that I'm a rabbit?
adviseScripts.speaker: Alice

adviseScripts.text: I join Alice in her hopping practice.
